 :tx/rationale "ADR-024 OBSERVATION 5: CLI AS MARKOV BLANKET. The CLI is the boundary between two epistemological systems: the store (formal, datom-based, append-only) and the LLM (statistical, attention-based, context-windowed). Like every boundary in the formalism, its coherence is measurable, its coverage is quantifiable, and its quality is learnable. The free energy principle (Friston): F = D_KL(model || reality) + H(observations | model). D_KL = F(S) divergence. H = observation entropy. The CLI minimizes free energy by optimizing the information channel between store and LLM. Command names, flag defaults, help text, error messages are ALL hypotheses about the LLM's natural ontology. Every 404'd command is a free data point. Every flag override is a signal the default is wrong."
